Dialogue: 4,0:00:31.98,0:00:34.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The picture is of \NChihaya and her mother,{\i0}
Dialogue: 4,0:00:34.75,0:00:36.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}arguing before the eyes \Nof that very brother.{\i0}
Dialogue: 4,0:00:37.91,0:00:42.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\i1}Incidentally, Chihaya's parents are divorced as of several months ago.{\i0}
Dialogue: 4,0:00:43.40,0:00:47.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\i1}Death in an accident. \NDomestic collapse. Divorce.{\i0}
Dialogue: 4,0:00:47.01,0:00:49.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\i1}Misfortune builds upon \Nitself around her.{\i0}
Dialogue: 4,0:00:51.24,0:00:56.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\i1}Placing a mask over that cursed reality, \NKisaragi Chihaya sings today once more,{\i0}
Dialogue: 4,0:00:56.93,0:00:59.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\i1}in front of fans who know nothing.{\i0}
Dialogue: 4,0:01:00.01,0:01:01.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell?!
Dialogue: 4,0:01:01.32,0:01:03.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They say it like everything's \NChihaya's fault!
Dialogue: 4,0:01:04.28,0:01:07.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The very writing is \Nfilled with malice.
Dialogue: 4,0:01:07.82,0:01:11.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I never knew Chihaya-san \Nhad a little brother...
Dialogue: 4,0:01:11.50,0:01:14.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Haruka-chan, did you know?
Dialogue: 4,0:01:14.74,0:01:16.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 4,0:01:17.90,0:01:20.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all true.
Dialogue: 4,0:01:20.44,0:01:22.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That I had a little brother.
Dialogue: 4,0:01:22.49,0:01:25.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That it's my fault he lost his life.
Dialogue: 4,0:01:26.13,0:01:30.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had heard about your \Nbrother from your parents,
Dialogue: 4,0:01:31.41,0:01:36.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but they said that you were simply there by \Ncoincidence, and that you were not to blame.
Dialogue: 4,0:01:37.55,0:01:40.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever my parents say, \Nit doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.57,0:01:40.20,Sign,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnHelveticaRounded LT Std Bd\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&HFFFFFF&\b1\blur1\an3\fs40\bord4\pos(173,428)\t(0,196,\3c&H5599C9&\c&HD7DCDE&)}{ts|15.46|Sketchbook top}Sketchbook
Dialogue: 4,0:01:42.47,0:01:45.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I– If I hadn't been there,
Dialogue: 4,0:01:45.69,0:01:48.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,my brother wouldn't have \Nbeen in that accident.
Dialogue: 4,0:01:49.13,0:01:50.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kisaragi-kun...
Dialogue: 4,0:01:50.75,0:01:51.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chihaya...
Dialogue: 4,0:01:51.71,0:01:54.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I {\i1}must{\i0\fscx60} {\r} keep on singing.
Dialogue: 4,0:01:55.11,0:01:56.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On my brother's behalf, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.47,0:02:04.22,Sign,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur0.5\fnCalibri\fs68\b1\an8\bord3\blur4\be3\1a&H00&\3a&H88&\c&HF4F4F4&\fad(940,929)\pos(386,558)}Episode {\b1\c&HAF7620&}20
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.47,0:02:04.22,Sign,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\fs78\bord3\blur4\be3\1a&H00&\3a&H55&\fnCalibri\b1\3c&H1F1F20&\pos(869,549)\fad(940,929)\c&HAF7620&}Prom{\c&HFFFFFF&}ise
Dialogue: 4,0:02:00.65,0:02:04.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}They couldn't have imagined \Na trump card like this.
Dialogue: 4,0:02:04.53,0:02:10.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,765 Pro's– No, Takagi's bitter face is dancing before my eyes!
Dialogue: 4,0:02:14.68,0:02:17.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So this is how you do things?
Dialogue: 4,0:02:18.61,0:02:20.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you trying to say?
Dialogue: 4,0:02:20.36,0:02:21.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You already know!
Dialogue: 4,0:02:21.75,0:02:23.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm telling you not to \Npull this petty crap!
Dialogue: 4,0:02:24.25,0:02:26.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only one playing dirty \Nhere is you, old ma–!
Dialogue: 4,0:02:26.45,0:02:28.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who do you think you're talking to?
Dialogue: 4,0:02:29.41,0:02:31.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I told you...
Dialogue: 4,0:02:31.20,0:02:34.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You lot just need to \Nshut up, follow orders,
Dialogue: 4,0:02:34.53,0:02:39.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and watch from the sidelines as Third-Rate Pro destroys itself.
Dialogue: 4,0:02:41.55,0:02:43.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are no abnormalities in her throat,
Dialogue: 4,0:02:43.78,0:02:46.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,nor is there anything \Npreventing her from vocalizing.
Dialogue: 4,0:02:46.55,0:02:51.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When it comes to this, "voice will not emerge when trying to sing,"
Dialogue: 4,0:02:51.04,0:02:54.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the origin is most likely \Npsychological in nature.
Dialogue: 4,0:02:55.03,0:02:58.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though there are cases where \Nsymptoms disappear with time,
Dialogue: 4,0:02:58.63,0:03:00.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,this isn't something I can...
Dialogue: 4,0:03:07.01,0:03:08.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yuu...{\i0}
Dialogue: 4,0:03:27.57,0:03:28.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sing!{\i0}
Dialogue: 4,0:03:28.68,0:03:29.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sing, Onee-chan!{\i0}
Dialogue: 4,0:03:31.34,0:03:34.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My little brother was \Nthe only audience I had.{\i0}
Dialogue: 4,0:03:35.42,0:03:36.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Until that day.{\i0}
Dialogue: 4,0:03:42.51,0:03:44.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I {\i1}must{\i0\fscx60} {\r} continue to sing."
Dialogue: 4,0:03:44.84,0:03:48.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I've got to keep singing. For Yuu."
Dialogue: 4,0:03:48.55,0:03:49.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's how I felt.
Dialogue: 4,0:03:51.07,0:03:53.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I can't sing for him anymore.
Dialogue: 4,0:03:54.52,0:03:56.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a failure.
Dialogue: 4,0:03:56.01,0:03:58.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Both as an idol \Nand as an older sister.
Dialogue: 4,0:04:00.74,0:04:02.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chihaya-chan...
Dialogue: 4,0:04:02.30,0:04:05.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chihaya, you shouldn't \Npressure yourself so much.
Dialogue: 4,0:04:05.46,0:04:07.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's put singing work on \Nthe back burner for a while.
Dialogue: 4,0:04:07.95,0:04:09.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, we'll give your \Nemotions a good rest–
Dialogue: 4,0:04:11.58,0:04:12.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that I can no longer sing,
Dialogue: 4,0:04:13.58,0:04:15.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't intend to continue \Nin this line of work.
Dialogue: 4,0:04:17.18,0:04:18.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chihaya...!
Dialogue: 4,0:04:18.75,0:04:22.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you might be able \Nto sing again, right?
Dialogue: 4,0:04:22.32,0:04:24.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I know you will!
Dialogue: 4,0:04:24.10,0:04:24.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So–
Dialogue: 4,0:04:26.47,0:04:29.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize for all the disturbance.
Dialogue: 4,0:04:29.38,0:04:30.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chihaya!
Dialogue: 4,0:04:30.56,0:04:31.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chihaya-chan!
Dialogue: 4,0:04:31.87,0:04:33.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 4,0:04:33.09,0:04:34.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care anymore.
Dialogue: 4,0:04:40.63,0:04:43.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are we live?! Sunday!
