Dialogue: 4,0:04:43.76,0:04:48.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chihaya's out with a cold today, so the two of us are coming to you live!
Dialogue: 4,0:04:48.40,0:04:50.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yay! We're pulling out the stops!
Dialogue: 4,0:04:50.69,0:04:53.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay then! We're starting \Ntoday with {\i1}this{\i0\fscx60} {\r} segment!
Dialogue: 4,0:04:54.79,0:04:56.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cameras have switched! {to indicate studio cameras are no longer active while the other segment runs}
Dialogue: 4,0:05:01.11,0:05:02.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Chihaya won't pick up?
Dialogue: 4,0:05:03.48,0:05:04.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}No.
Dialogue: 4,0:05:04.61,0:05:08.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}When I go to her flat, she won't \Neven answer the door.
Dialogue: 4,0:05:08.08,0:05:12.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I do leave food so that \Nshe keeps eating, but...
Dialogue: 4,0:05:13.11,0:05:14.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about her parents?
Dialogue: 4,0:05:15.21,0:05:17.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even when I explained \Nthe situation to them,
Dialogue: 4,0:05:17.00,0:05:18.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they'd just repeat, \N"We can't do anything."
Dialogue: 4,0:05:19.79,0:05:23.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though this is exactly the kind of time I'd like them to be her support.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.17,0:05:25.42,Sign,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnZaratustra Assemblee\fs24\c&H2C4F36&\alpha&H44&\fax0.058\frz32.184\pos(654,420)}Missed calls
